## Code Example

```javascript
import http from 'k6/http';
import { sleep } from 'k6';
import { Rate } from 'k6/metrics';

const cacheHitRate = new Rate('cache_hit_rate');
const latency = new Trend('latency_ms');

export const options = {
  stages: [
    { duration: '2m', target: 10000 },
    { duration: '30s', target: 50000 },
    { duration: '1m', target: 50000 },
    { duration: '2m', target: 0 },
  ],
  thresholds: {
    'http_req_duration@p95': ['<500'],
    'http_req_duration@p99': ['<1000'],
    'cache_hit_rate': ['>0.95'],
  },
};

export default function () {
  const longTailKeys = generateLongTailDistribution();
  const res = http.get(`https://api.example.com/video/${longTailKeys[Math.floor(Math.random() * longTailKeys.length)]}`);

  cacheHitRate.add(res.headers['X-Cache-Hit'] === 'true');
  latency.add(res.timings.duration);
  sleep(0.01);
}

function generateLongTailDistribution() {
  const hotKeys = Array.from({ length: 100 }, (_, i) => `hot_${i}`);
  const warmKeys = Array.from({ length: 1000 }, (_, i) => `warm_${i}`);
  const coldKeys = Array.from({ length: 10000 }, (_, i) => `cold_${i}`);
  return [...hotKeys, ...warmKeys, ...coldKeys];
}
```

## Workload Model

- **Ramp phase**: 2 minutes from 0 to 10k QPS (baseline)
- **Burst phase**: 30 seconds spike to 50k QPS (peak)
- **Sustain phase**: 1 minute at 50k QPS (stress test)
- **Cool-down**: 2 minutes ramp down to 0
- **Request distribution**: 60% hot keys, 30% warm keys, 10% cold/long-tail keys

## Metrics to Collect

| Metric | Target | Purpose |
|--------|--------|---------|
| p95 Latency | < 500ms | Validate acceptable user experience |
| p99 Latency | < 1000ms | Ensure tail requests perform |
| CDN Hit Rate | > 95% | Verify edge cache effectiveness |
| Redis Hit Rate | > 80% (of misses) | Validate regional cache |
| Pod Spin-up Time | < 60s | Confirm HPA responsiveness |
| Origin Error Rate | < 0.1% | Detect stampede/overload |

## Failure Modes to Test

1. **Cache Stampede**: When cache expires simultaneously across many requests, causing origin overload
2. **Pod Thrashing**: HPA scaling up/down too aggressively, causing instability
3. **CDN Cold Starts**: Edge caches not warmed, causing origin traffic surge
4. **Redis Connection Exhaustion**: Under burst, connection pool limits reached
5. **Custom Metric Lag**: qps_per_service metric delayed, causing delayed HPA reactions

