## Approach

### Workload Strategy

Design a realistic traffic mix representing production patterns: 70% standard payments, 20% recurring, 10% high-value requiring additional fraud scrutiny. Use warm-up phases (5-10 minutes) to reach steady state before measuring. Implement ramp-up and ramp-down profiles to avoid cold-start anomalies.

### Data Strategy

Generate synthetic test data with realistic distributions: card BINs, merchant categories, transaction amounts following Pareto or log-normal distributions. Pre-seed idempotency keys to validate exactly-once processing. Maintain referential integrity across test runs with deterministic data generation.

### Metrics Collection

Instrument all service boundaries with distributed tracing (e.g., Jaeger, Zipkin). Capture: end-to-end latency percentiles (p50, p95, p99, p99.9), throughput per service, Kafka consumer lag, error rates by type, and queue depths. Monitor backpressure signals including producer buffer saturation and consumer fetch delays.

### Failure Mode Injection

- **Gateway Throttling**: Use rate-limiting middleware or Chaos Mesh to simulate 1,800 rps cap and observe queue buildup and timeout behavior
- **Outage Simulation**: Inject 2% failure rates at random intervals using fault injection; measure retry logic effectiveness and circuit breaker activation
- **Partition Rebalancing**: Trigger Kafka rebalances mid-test to observe consumer recovery and processing gaps

